FBIS3-55329 "drsov007_a_94008" FBIS-SOV-94-007 Document Type:Daily Report 11 Jan 1994 RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS Filatov: Nuclear Arms To Be Main Topic of Summit LD1101125894 Moscow Mayak Radio Network in Russian 1200 GMT 11 Jan 94 LD1101125894 Moscow Mayak Radio Network Language: Russian Article Type:BFN [Text] The main political topic of the upcoming talks in Moscow between the U.S. and Russian presidents will be the problem of nuclear weapons on the territory of the former Soviet Union, Sergey Filatov, head of the Russian Federation president's staff, told a RIA correspondent. In his view, the main problem is finding a way to ensure that there is only one nuclear state, Russia, on this territory.
